         <div>
            <head>"RUSSIAN CATHEDRAL"</head>
            <lg>
               <l enjamb="yes">Bow down my soul in worship very low</l>
               <l enjamb="no">And in the holy silences be lost.</l>
               <l enjamb="no">Bow down before the marble man of woe,</l>
               <l enjamb="no">Bow down before the singing angel host.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg>
               <l enjamb="no">What jewelled glory fills my spirit's eye!</l>
               <l enjamb="no">What golden grandeur moves the depths of me!</l>
               <l enjamb="yes">The soaring arches lift me up on high</l>
               <l enjamb="no">Taking my breath with their rare symmetry.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg>
               <l enjamb="yes">Bow down my soul and let the wondrous light</l>
               <l enjamb="yes">Of Beauty bathe thee from her lofty throne</l>
               <l enjamb="no">Bow down before the wonder of man's might.</l>
               <l enjamb="no">Bow down in worship, humble and alone;</l>
               <l enjamb="yes">Bow lowly down before the sacred sight</l>
               <l enjamb="no">Of man's divinity alive in stone.</l> 
            </lg>
            <byline>Claud McKay</byline>
         </div>
